<paragraph blockId="15.[810,1420,1234,1641]" pageId="15" pageNumber="1012">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[810,971,1376,1400]" pageId="15" pageNumber="1012">Identification.</emphasis>
Under hindwing with prominent white spots and one in cell, some may be absent; female with an additional spot near inner edge and a second smaller one above it on under forewing, spread over whitish area near under forewing inner edge; male upper forewing spots well marked, a prominent pale brand with the lower end of the brand nearer to base than to outer edge, no spot near inner edge, upper hindwing usually unmarked.
</paragraph>
